---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Apps for A/B Testing in 2026';
const description = 'Compare Shopify email apps for A/B testing by experiment controls, audience splits, reporting, pricing context, source links, and practical tradeoffs.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Lifecycle tests across detailed segments','Flexible flows, segments, and analytics','Requires disciplined test design and sample sizes','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation'],['Omnisend','Retail campaign tests across email and SMS','Accessible multichannel campaign workflows','Cross-channel comparisons need care','https://www.omnisend.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Sequenzy','Lean teams testing sequence variations','Simple workflow iteration','May have less advanced experimentation depth','https://sequenzy.io/'],['Drip','DTC teams measuring revenue-oriented experiments','Commerce automation and reporting','Attribution assumptions still require scrutiny','https://www.drip.com/features'],['Brevo','Campaign testing with broad messaging needs','Email and transactional coverage','More manual ecommerce cohort analysis','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">A/B testing is valuable only when the audience split, outcome, timing, and exclusions are clear. Changing a subject line on a tiny or mixed cohort does not establish a universal performance claim.</p><p>We prioritize usable experiment controls, Shopify event access, holdout thinking, and reporting that separates clicks from incremental orders. Confirm current pricing and analytics limits from official sources.</p><h2>Shortlist for experiments</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>First experiment</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[0]==='Klaviyo'?'Flow-message test':a[0]==='Omnisend'?'Email/SMS campaign test':a[0]==='Sequenzy'?'Sequence timing test':a[0]==='Drip'?'Repeat-purchase cohort':'Campaign variant test'}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for A/B testing</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[0]} is useful when the team can hold the audience rule, offer, and measurement window constant while changing one meaningful variable. Shopify event access helps, but it does not remove the need to define the unit of analysis.</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[2]}. Start with one high-volume lifecycle message, document the hypothesis, and include a holdout where practical. Report confidence and limitations honestly; avoid turning a directional result into an unsupported revenue percentage.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}; supports a controlled experiment; can use Shopify behavior.</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}; audience size and reporting complexity affect cost.</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Verify official plans for contacts, sends, seats, reporting, and SMS.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Experiment priority</th><th>Start with</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Segmented lifecycle tests</td><td>Klaviyo</td><td>Flexible event and flow controls.</td></tr><tr><td>Simple sequence iteration</td><td>Sequenzy</td><td>Focused workflows are easy to compare.</td></tr><tr><td>Commerce retention analysis</td><td>Drip</td><td>Useful for repeat-purchase cohorts.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>See the <a href="/shopify-email">Shopify email overview</a>, <a href="/alternatives">alternatives library</a>, and <a href="/guides/revenue-attribution">revenue-attribution guide</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
